body_text.text:
A 10-fold serial dilution of SARS-CoV-2 RNA was amplified to determine the lower limit of detection with the RT-LAMP kit. Fig. 1
shows the results for the detection of real-time turbidity with the LA-200 turbidimeter. The minimum amount of RNA detected was 1.0 × 101 copies/µL, which was achieved within 35 min in this procedure. After measurement, turbidity of the reaction solution could be observed visually under natural light (Fig. 2
).
